{
  "texts": [
    "Recall that D k (X) stands for the space of metric k-currents on X.",
    "Since Lip b (X) = Lip c (X), any element T of D k (X) restricts, by definition, to a map T: K(X) → R. We shall identify T = T |K(X).",
    "Theorem 3.2.",
    "Let X be a compact metric space and k ∈ N. Then D k (X) ⊂ C(K(X)).Proof.",
    "This follows from the joint continuity property.Corollary 3.3."
  ]
}